		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName> <date>April 11<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1849</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Reverd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">My Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">Your favr. of <date>9th</date> Ult was duly reced.<lb/> and be assured I have not been unmindful of your<lb/> valuable suggestions.  All the points in your circular<lb/> are calculated to have an important bearing on the<lb/> future dignity and distinctness of our holy religion<lb/> but the congregation of which I am a member having<lb/> taken ground differing so widely from the views con&#61;<lb/>&#61;templated by the proposed convention I can see no pros&#45;<lb/>&#61;pect of our cooperation therefore cannot recom&#61;<lb/>&#61;mend a delegate being sent.  And moreover&#44; on<lb/> a former occasion when all the Israelites of the city<lb/> formd but one congregation&#44; a similar suggestion<lb/> was submitted from <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> to a very full mee&#45;<lb/>&#61;ting when by an almost unanimous vote it was re&#61;<lb/>solved that we could not coalesce.  Still I am satisfied<lb/> the effort is a very laudable one and if the association can<lb/> be organized its measures must have a general and sater&#45;<lb/>&#61;tory influence.  You have my earnest prayer for its early<lb/> consummation</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You will please find enclosed twelve 25&#47;100 the<lb/> amt. Of your a&#47;c as stated and let me add that I entertain<lb/> no asperities towards <persName>Mr. Hart</persName> or any other person who may<lb/> differ with me in opinion&#44; and in future if you desire it I<lb/> will settle with him   Very respectfully yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">Joshua Lazarus</persName></p>
				<p>&#40;charge the quarter to the next a&#47;c&#41;</p>
		</body>
